From cou.: 7 The synthesis of the hexaviologen–phosphorus dendrimer (HV12+) was achieved in 82% yield (Scheme 1a and ESI†) following the reaction of the hexachlorodendrimer (3) with 1-methyl-4,4′-bipyridinium (MB+) in MeCN. HV·12PF6 was obtained quantitatively from the water soluble intermediate HV·6I·6Cl after counter ion exchange with a saturated solution of ammonium hexafluorophosphate (NH4PF6) in H2O.14f The resulting hexaviologen dendrimer (HV·12PF6) was fully characterized (see ESI†) by 1H, 31P and 13C NMR spectroscopies and mass spectrometry. The redox-induced switching of HV·12PF6 was investigated by electrochemistry and UV-Vis-NIR absorption spectroscopy.
From Soup: 7 The synthesis of the hexaviologen–phosphorus dendrimer ( HV 12+ ) was achieved in 82% yield ( Scheme 1a and ESI † ) following the reaction of the hexachlorodendrimer ( 3 ) with 1-methyl-4,4′-bipyridinium ( MB + ) in MeCN. HV ·12PF 6 was obtained quantitatively from the water soluble intermediate HV ·6I·6Cl after counter ion exchange with a saturated solution of ammonium hexafluorophosphate (NH 4 PF 6 ) in H 2 O . 14f The resulting hexaviologen dendrimer ( HV ·12PF 6 ) was fully characterized (see ESI † ) by 1 H, 31 P and 13 C NMR spectroscopies and mass spectrometry . The redox-induced switching of HV ·12PF 6 was investigated by electrochemistry and UV-Vis-NIR absorption spectroscopy .
