From cou.: 8 The redox-activated intramolecular dimerization is depicted in Scheme 1b. In the fully oxidized state of HV12+, the individual BIPY2+ units of the functionalized core repel each other as a consequence of Coulombic repulsion. A one-electron reduction of each of the BIPY2+ units results in the formation of the BIPY˙+ radical cation, which very quickly undergoes intramolecular π-dimerization with its nearest neighbor on the central core. Although both BIPY˙+ units are still positively charged, spin pairing of the radicals into a singlet state in addition to their reduced charge overpowers the electrostatic repulsion.
From Soup: 8 The redox-activated intramolecular dimerization is depicted in Scheme 1b . In the fully oxidized state of HV 12+ , the individual BIPY 2+ units of the functionalized core repel each other as a consequence of Coulombic repulsion. A one-electron reduction of each of the BIPY 2+ units results in the formation of the BIPY˙ + radical cation , which very quickly undergoes intramolecular π-dimerization with its nearest neighbor on the central core. Although both BIPY˙ + units are still positively charged, spin pairing of the radicals into a singlet state in addition to their reduced charge overpowers the electrostatic repulsion.
