From Soup: 35 Although the shifts in the redox potentials are small ( E 1 1/2 ( BMV 2+ ) − E 1 1/2 ( HV 12+ ) = 40 mV, the fact that the number of electrons transferred is six still leads to large values of β Dim . If one speculates about a system composed of only two BIPY˙ + units linked together covalently with a comparable value of β Dim , one would expect the shift in the redox-potentials to be three times large. Previous reports showed that this is indeed the case. 26 Digitally simulated CVs (see ESI † ) based on this proposed mechanism match well with our experimental data . With eqn (6) in hand, we have now a means of evaluating β Dim , which we have done in a variety of solvents ( β Dim = 1.3 × 10 4 in DMF, see Table S1 in the ESI † ).
