From Soup: 36 In order to provide additional evidence for the intramolecular dimerization of the BIPY˙ + radical units within HV D 6( ˙ +) , we carried out variable concentration spectrophotometric titrations monitoring absorption in the UV/Vis/NIR region. Reduction of HV 12+ and BMV 2+ to the corresponding radical cations was achieved under a continuous flow of argon in less than 1 h by vigorous stirring with activated zinc dust in argon-purged MeCN (see ESI † ). As a control, we first examined the variable concentration spectra of BMV˙ + . The spectra ( Fig. 2a ) reveal two prominent absorption bands at 395 and 600 nm, which are the characteristic of the BIPY˙ + radical cation monomer.
