From cou.: 38 In order to provide additional evidence for the intramolecular dimerization of the BIPY˙+ radical units within HVD6(˙+), we carried out variable concentration spectrophotometric titrations monitoring absorption in the UV/Vis/NIR region. Reduction of HV12+ and BMV2+ to the corresponding radical cations was achieved under a continuous flow of argon in less than 1 h by vigorous stirring with activated zinc dust in argon-purged MeCN (see ESI†). As a control, we first examined the variable concentration spectra of BMV˙+. The spectra (Fig. 2a) reveal two prominent absorption bands at 395 and 600 nm, which are the characteristic of the BIPY˙+ radical cation monomer.
From Soup: 38 In order to gain insight into the nature of the pimerization process we have performed density functional theory calculations at the M06/6-31G(d,p) level, 27 a computational approach that has been shown to provide good results for inclusion complexes of BIPY˙ + radical cations . 15 Due to the large size of the system of interest, our calculations ( Fig. 3 ) were performed on a simplified model denoted BV 4+ where four of the six BMV 2+ units of HV 12+ were replaced by methyl groups.
